<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The two taxa were both proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuetzing, FT" journalOrPublisher="W. Koehne, Nordhausen" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 152" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.64360" refId="B10" refString="Kuetzing, FT, 1844. Die kieselschaligen Bacillarien oder Diatomeen. W. Koehne, Nordhausen: 1 - 152, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.64360" title="Die kieselschaligen Bacillarien oder Diatomeen" url="10.5962/bhl.title.64360" year="1844">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kützing">Kuetzing</normalizedToken>
(1844
</bibRefCitation>
, p. 80) and therefore have the same priority. In similar cases, Article 11.5 of the ICN rules that &quot;the first such choice to be effectively published establishes the priority of the chosen name&quot;.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<bibRefCitation author="Grunow, A" journalOrPublisher="Beitraege zur Palaeontologie Oesterreich-Ugarns und des Orients" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="136 - 159" refId="B5" refString="Grunow, A, 1882. Beitraege zur Kenntniss de fossilen Diatomeen Oesterreich-Ugarns. Beitraege zur Palaeontologie Oesterreich-Ugarns und des Orients 2: 136 - 159" title="Beitraege zur Kenntniss de fossilen Diatomeen Oesterreich-Ugarns." volume="2" year="1882">Grunow (1882)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the new combination and the new status of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella excisa" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="excisa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cymbella excisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Grunow" authorityYear="1882" baseAuthorityName="Kuetz." class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella affinis subsp. var. var. excisa" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="affinis" subSpecies="var." variety="excisa">Cymbella affinis var. excisa</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kütz">Kuetz</normalizedToken>
.) Grunow. This was the first publication that defined the priority of the epithet 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Kuetz" authorityYear="1844" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="affinis" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
over 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="excisa" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="excisa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">excisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the specific level. Therefore, the name 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Kuetz" authorityYear="1844" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella affinis" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cymbella affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be considered to be the name of the species when 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella excisa" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="excisa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cymbella excisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Kuetz" authorityYear="1844" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella affinis" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cymbella affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are considered to be the same species, in conformity with Article 11.5 of the ICN (
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill, J" journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 240" refId="B14" refString="McNeill, J, Barrie, FR, Buck, WR, Demoulin, V, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Marhold, K, Prado, J, Prud'Homme Van Reine, WF, Smith, GF, Wiersema, JH, Turland, NJ, 2012. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Melbourne Code) adopted by the Eighteenth International Botanical Congress Melbourne, Australia, July 2011. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein: 1 - 240" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Melbourne Code) adopted by the Eighteenth International Botanical Congress Melbourne, Australia, July 2011" year="2012">McNeill et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Kuetz" authorityYear="1844" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella affinis" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cymbella affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
valves sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Patrick, R" journalOrPublisher="Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 213" refId="B17" refString="Patrick, R, Reimer, CW, 1975. The diatoms of the United States. Volume 2, Part 1. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 13: 1 - 213" title="The diatoms of the United States. Volume 2, Part 1." volume="13" year="1975">Patrick and Reimer (1975</bibRefCitation>
, p. 57) have similar outlines as 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Kuetz" authorityYear="1844" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella affinis" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cymbella affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the type population, but higher range of length and breadth values (length: 20-50 vs. 22.5-26.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
; breadth: 7-12 vs. 7.0-8.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, respectively). However, these authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Patrick, R" journalOrPublisher="Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 213" refId="B17" refString="Patrick, R, Reimer, CW, 1975. The diatoms of the United States. Volume 2, Part 1. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 13: 1 - 213" title="The diatoms of the United States. Volume 2, Part 1." volume="13" year="1975">Patrick and Reimer 1975</bibRefCitation>
), included representatives of different localities that could encompass different varieties subscribed to this taxon. The density of striae in the material from USA was similar in the middle part of the valve compared to the type material (9-11 vs. 9-12 striae in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, respectively) and lower when comparing them close to the ends of the valvae (12-14 vs. 11-18 striae in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, respectively) (
<bibRefCitation author="Patrick, R" journalOrPublisher="Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 213" refId="B17" refString="Patrick, R, Reimer, CW, 1975. The diatoms of the United States. Volume 2, Part 1. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 13: 1 - 213" title="The diatoms of the United States. Volume 2, Part 1." volume="13" year="1975">Patrick and Reimer 1975</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella excisa subsp. var. var. procera" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="excisa" subSpecies="var." variety="procera">Cymbella excisa var. procera</taxonomicName>
Krammer (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–28" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 28. Cymbella affinis species complex 1 - 7 Cymbella affinis Kuetz. var. affinis 8 - 14 Cymbella affinis var. excisa (Kuetz.) Grunow, specimens from Trieste in preparation BM 18543 11 Lectotype, designated here 15 - 21 Cymbella affinis var. excisa [- Cymbella excisa sensu Krammer], specimens from Trieste in preparation 1131 IOK 16 Isolectotype, designated here 22 - 28 Cymbella affinis var. neoprocera W. Silva, specimens from Germany in preparation 212 A IOK, holotype 22 Lectotype, designated here. Scale bar: 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.53.4782.figures1-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/47588" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">22-28</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella excisa subsp. var. var. angusta" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="excisa" subSpecies="var." variety="angusta">Cymbella excisa var. angusta</taxonomicName>
Krammer (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 29–42" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 29 - 42. Cymbella affinis species complex 29 - 35 Cymbella affinis var. angusta (Krammer) W. Silva, specimens from Croatia in preparation 752 IOK, holotype 29 Lectotype, designated here 36 - 42 Cymbella affinis var. subcapitata (Krammer) W. Silva, specimens from Hungary in preparation 717 IOK, holotype 39 Lectotype, designated here. Scale bar: 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.53.4782.figures29-42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/47589" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">39-35</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella excisa subsp. var. var. subcapitata" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="excisa" subSpecies="var." variety="subcapitata">Cymbella excisa var. subcapitata</taxonomicName>
Krammer (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 29–42" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 29 - 42. Cymbella affinis species complex 29 - 35 Cymbella affinis var. angusta (Krammer) W. Silva, specimens from Croatia in preparation 752 IOK, holotype 29 Lectotype, designated here 36 - 42 Cymbella affinis var. subcapitata (Krammer) W. Silva, specimens from Hungary in preparation 717 IOK, holotype 39 Lectotype, designated here. Scale bar: 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.53.4782.figures29-42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/47589" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">36-42</figureCitation>
) also appear to be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Kuetz" authorityYear="1844" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella affinis" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cymbella affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the types show slight differences in their outlines and metric characteristics (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Metric features of the material of the complex Cymbella affinis / tumidula / turgidula analyzed in this study (n = 29 - 34 individuals)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/2530DF387556299AC796ED5FBC0D74A2" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" tableUuid="2530DF387556299AC796ED5FBC0D74A2">1</tableCitation>
). Thus, all these taxa are here transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Kuetz" authorityYear="1844" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella affinis" order="Cymbellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cymbella affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using their respective infraspecific epithet.
</paragraph>
